narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Don't take it unless you absolutely have to!!! One of the worst classes I've taken at Yale. Annoying pointless problem sets, a multiple choice midterm, and long, brutal powerpoint lectures. Seriously, don't.
If it's a requirement, then don't stress it too much. There is a pset due every week or two. The midterm is multiple choice. The final and final paper are more challenging but not impossible.
The course gives an overview of air pollution control technologies. It doesn't really require too much math.
